The paper deals with stability and analysis of multi-agent network systems, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of social and information networks (cs.SI), multi-agent systems (cs.MA), and control systems (cs.SY). The paper also discusses game-theoretic settings, which falls under the sub-category of theoretical computer science (cs.GT). Finally, the paper introduces a new framework for analysis, which could potentially fall under the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG).
